====Talking to Dr Fenkenstrain again====
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Do you know where I could find body parts?}}
** '''Player:''' Do you know where I could find body parts?
** '''Dr Fenkenstrain:''' The soil of Morytania is unique in its ability to preserve the bodies of the dead, which is one reason why I have chosen to carry out my experiments here.
** '''Dr Fenkenstrain:''' I recommend digging up some graves in the local area. To the south-east you will find the Haunted Woods; I believe there are many graves there.
** '''Dr Fenkenstrain:''' There is also a mausoleum on an island west of this castle. I expect the bodies that are buried there to be extremely well preserved, as they were wealthy in life.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Remind me what you want me to do.}}
** '''Player:''' What do you want me to do, again?
** '''Dr Fenkenstrain:''' I need you to get me enough dead body parts for me to stitch together a complete body, which I plan to bring to life.
** '''Player:''' Right...okay...if you insist.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Why are you trying to make this creature?}}
** '''Player:''' Why do you want to make a creature?
** '''Dr Fenkenstrain:''' I came to the land of Morytania many years ago, to find a safe sanctuary for my experiments. This abandoned castle suited my purposes exactly.
** '''Player:''' What were you experimenting in?
** '''Dr Fenkenstrain:''' Oh, perfectly innocent experiments - for the good of mankind.
** '''Player:''' Then why did you need to come to Morytania?
** '''Dr Fenkenstrain:''' Enough questions, now. Get back to your work.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Will this creature put me out of a job?}}
** '''Player:''' Will this creature put me out of a job?
** '''Dr Fenkenstrain:''' No, my friend. I have a very special purpose in mind for this creature.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I must get back to work, sir.}}
** '''Player:''' I must get back to work, sir.
** {{tact|end}}

==Decapitated head==
===Talking to the Gardener Ghost===
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Tell me about Fenkenstrain.}}
** '''Player:''' Can you tell me anything about Fenkenstrain?
** {{tcond|If the player is not wearing the amulet of ghostspeak:}}
*** {{tbox|The Headless Gardener's neck twitches at you, but the lack of any head prevents him from speaking.}}
** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the amulet of ghostspeak:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Ghostspeak amulet detail.png|You feel power emanate from the Amulet of Ghostspeak, and the air around you vibrates with the ghostly voice of the Headless Gardener...}}
*** '''Player:''' Can you tell me anything about Fenkenstrain?
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Oi could tell you a few things about old Fenky, yeah.
*** '''Player:''' Go on.
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Once, this castle were full o' good folk - my friends. Fenky was just the castle doctor you know, to the Lord and the castle folk.
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' I don't know what happened to them all, but one by one they all disappeared. When they were gone a while, I went an dug graves for 'em, in the forest.
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' After a while there weren't no-one left, but the Lord, Fenkenstrain, and meself.
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Old Fenky sent me into the Forest to dig 'im a pit. Never said what for. Then would you believe it, someone chops me head off.
*** '''Player:''' Did you see who did it, before ... 
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Before oi kicked the bucket, you mean?
*** '''Player:''' Umm...
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Don't worry yourself, I'm not worried about bein' dead. Worse things could happen, I suppose.
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' One thing I do know is, there ain't no Lord of the castle anymore, 'cept for old Fenky. Makes you think a bit, don't it?
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What happened to your head?}}
** '''Player:''' Can you tell me anything about Fenkenstrain?
** {{tcond|If the player is not wearing the amulet of ghostspeak:}}
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the amulet of ghostspeak:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Ghostspeak amulet detail.png|You feel power emanate from the Amulet of Ghostspeak, and the air around you vibrates with the ghostly voice of the Headless Gardener...}}
**** '''Player:''' What happened to your head?
**** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Oi was in the old 'aunted Forest to the south, diggin' a pit for moi old maaster, old Fenkenstrain, when would you believe it, someone chops me head off. Awful bad luck, weren't it?
**** '''Player:''' Oh yes, dreadful bad luck.
**** '''Gardener Ghost:''' So oi thinks to meself, I don't needs any 'ead to be gettin on with me gardenin', long as I got me hands and me spade. 
**** '''Player:''' Would you show me where the place was?
**** {{tcond|If the player already found the head:}}
***** '''Gardener Ghost:''' No mate, you've found my head already, oi think.
***** {{tact|end}}
**** {{tcond|If the player does not have the head:}}
***** {{tact|The Gardener Ghost follows the player}}
***** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Well, oi s'pose oi've got 10 minutes to spare.
***** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What's your name?}}
** '''Player:''' Can you tell me anything about Fenkenstrain?
** {{tcond|If the player is not wearing the amulet of ghostspeak:}}
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the amulet of ghostspeak:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Ghostspeak amulet detail.png|You feel power emanate from the Amulet of Ghostspeak, and the air around you vibrates with the ghostly voice of the Headless Gardener...}}
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Me name? It's been a moivellous long while, mate, since I had any use for such a thing as a name.
*** '''Player:''' Don't worry, I was just trying to make conversation.
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' No, no, I can't be havin' that - I'll remember in a minute-
*** '''Player:''' Please, don't worry.
*** '''Gardener Ghost:''' Lestwit, that's it! Ed Lestwit!
